  "texts": [
    "However, since 'remote eye tracker' is already an established term in the field, we will use it in this article.",
    "Importantly, since gaze coordinates are recorded in world coordinates (e.g., a screen) with a head-boxed eye tracker, the AOI analysis would still be as simple as in the head-restricted case.",
    "In the head-restricted and head-boxed examples above, we have assumed a fixed world in the form of an image presented on a computer screen.",
    "However, the visual stimulus may also move relative to the screen, for example when dynamic visual stimuli such as videos are used.",
    "Due to the appearance, disappearance, and displacements of objects in the video, a pixel coordinate (x, y) on the screen no longer maps to a unique object in the video, making it challenging to count how much time participants spend looking at the objects."
  ],
